<p>50 Patients are randomly nursed on one of two types of mattresses, and after three days they are assessed for signs of pressure ulcers. (bedsores):</p>
<p>————— ——————- ————————- frequency some pressure ulcers (D) no pressure ulcers (not D) mattress type I 8 12 mattress type II 10 20 ————— ——————- ————————-</p>
<p>We want to know whether pressure ulcer formation is (in)dependent on the mattress type used. mattress type. Indicate which of the following reasoning is correct.</p>
</p>]]></text>
</questiontext>
<generalfeedback format="html">
<text><![CDATA[<p>
</p>]]></text>
</generalfeedback>
<penalty>0</penalty>
<defaultgrade>1</defaultgrade>
<shuffleanswers>false</shuffleanswers>
<single>true</single>
<answernumbering>abc</answernumbering>
<answer fraction="0" format="html">
<text><![CDATA[<p>
Dependent, because P(D ∩ I) ≠ 0
</p>]]></text>
<feedback format="html">
<text><![CDATA[<p>
Dependent, because P(D ∩ I) ≠ 0: Incorrect
</p>]]></text>
</feedback>
</answer>
<answer fraction="100" format="html">
<text><![CDATA[<p>
Dependent, because P(D | I) ≠ P(D)
</p>]]></text>
<feedback format="html">
<text><![CDATA[<p>
Dependent, because P(D | I) ≠ P(D): Correct
</p>]]></text>
</feedback>
</answer>
<answer fraction="0" format="html">
<text><![CDATA[<p>
Independent, because P(D | I) = P(I)
</p>]]></text>
<feedback format="html">
<text><![CDATA[<p>
Independent, because P(D | I) = P(I): Incorrect
</p>]]></text>
</feedback>
</answer>
<answer fraction="0" format="html">
<text><![CDATA[<p>
Independent, because P(D ∪ I) = P(D) + P(I) - P(D ∩ I)
</p>]]></text>
<feedback format="html">
<text><![CDATA[<p>
Independent, because P(D ∪ I) = P(D) + P(I) - P(D ∩ I): Incorrect
</p>]]></text>
</feedback>
</answer>
